    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - ELECTRONIC ENGINES, DT-466E, I-530E AND T-444E
        - Description - ATS
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
        <title>ATS</title>
        <para>The ambient Air Temperature Sensor (ATS) is a thermistor type sensor that has a variable resistance which
            changes when exposed to different temperatures. The ECM measures the signal from the sensor and uses the
            data to adjust timing and fuel rate to limit smoke emissions in cold weather starting.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
